This paper is primarily focused on defending against timing analysis attacks on web traffic, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the performance evaluation of the proposed solution under different network conditions, which is related to computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The privacy properties of the proposed solution are also discussed, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of the proposed solution, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
